{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"7f5fda5c-2697-4b43-ae15-141c51928b96","content":"The template is **not quite ready** for NuGet publishing. Here's my assessment:\n\n**Missing (important):**\n- **`$schema`** — Add `\"$schema\": \"http://json.schemastore.org/template\"` for validation support.\n- **`description`** — Required for NuGet discoverability. Without it, the listing will have no summary.\n- **`preferNameDirectory`** — Recommended as `true` for `project`-type templates.\n\n**Placeholder values to update:**\n- `author` is `\"My Company\"` — use your real org/author name.\n- `identity` uses `MyCompany` — update to match your actual package namespace.\n\n**Looks good:**\n- `shortName`, `sourceName`, `classifications`, `tags`, and `symbols` are all well-formed.\n- Framework choices for `net8.0`/`net9.0` are valid.\n\nIn short: add a `description`, set `preferNameDirectory`, update the placeholder author/identity, and optionally add the `$schema` — then it's ready to pack.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"f2a655a9-b293-42c6-a17a-f8331d4d9097","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"Let me review the template.json for NuGet publishing readiness. I need to check for:\n\n1. **`$schema`** — Missing. Should reference `http://json.schemastore.org/template` for validation.\n2. **`identity`** — Present. Looks fine.\n3. **`name`** — Present. Looks fine.\n4. **`shortName`** — Present. Looks fine.\n5. **`sourceName`** — Present. Good for namespace replacement.\n6. **`author`** — Present but generic (\"My Company\"). Should be updated for production.\n7. **`classifications`** — Present. \n\nThe tags look good with language and type specified. I'm noticing several missing fields that matter for NuGet discoverability: `description` is the most critical gap, while `preferNameDirectory` is recommended for project templates, and `groupIdentity` would be useful if there are related templates. The `author` field needs to be more specific, and while the schema reference isn't blocking, it's a nice-to-have for validation.\n\nI should also check whether there's a .nuspec or .csproj file handling the packaging configuration.","outputTokens":589,"requestId":"040F:3A0665:A71A5F:D16723:6A012A7A"},"id":"8a3bf91a-2886-49df-9826-a960aee2eba6","timestamp":"2026-05-11T01:01:59.134Z","parentId":"98cf456e-4390-4589-a90c-0661c42ce075"}
